tems&#34; class=link_owner&gt;&#xA;  Most tech teams have been missing a key point when evaluating AI systems&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#most-tech-teams-have-been-missing-a-key-point-when-evaluating-ai-systems&#34; class=&#34;link icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#anchor-link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s not new. Even back in the classical ML days, I noticed this pattern:&lt;br&gt;&#xA;we stuck to abstract, generic metrics (accuracy, F1-score, etc.) instead of designing domain-specific ones that truly reflect business value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
